===Noun===
'''vacation''' ([[vacations]])

#(''US'') Leisure time away from work and devoted to rest or pleasure.
#(''US'') The act of making legally void. 
#The act of vacating something; moving out of something.
#: ''The Conservative Party's '''vacation''' of the centre ground gave an opportunity to its opponents.''
#A holiday period for a law court or university. 

<!--====Usage Note====
Definition 4 is found throughout the English-speaking world; definition 1 is restricted to the United States.-->
